or with additional properties in addition to the materials which 
do not have analogs. The term ``properties'' is understood here 
in a broad sense, including both the physical, mechanical, and 
chemical characteristics and the structure of the surface, 
geometrical dimensions and shape, allowances, etc. The concepts 
of ``metal,'' ``material,'' and ``metal products'' overlap in a 
certain sense. 


